{"id":"5e9c2e5e9b6559241525d819","artists":["5e9b68fe7a1236eccfeb20e0"],"title":"New: Grandpa Was A Lion – Paris/Post-Acid","content":"<p>Artwork by <a href=\".</p><p>./music/9346-new-grandpa-was-a-lion-dancerflying-birds/www.katarinasoskic.net\">Katarina Soskic</a></p>\n<p>Over the last 6 days or so, <strong><a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/pages/Grandpa-Was-A-Lion/149221175111693\">Grandpa Was a Lion</a></strong> have been slowly dropping unheard demos of early material. The same beautifully withered vocals are present as ever, with each phrase sounding like a last gasp of hope or devotion. The weak and torn guitar notes elevate the music even further, perfectly mirroring the brokenly soulful tones of the vocals. Out of the 7 cuts dropped, we’ve established 2 highlights, <em><strong>Paris</strong></em> and <strong><em>Post-Acid</em></strong>, that are worthy as a starting point.</p>\n<p>So sit back, grab some tissues and prepare to be transported. Then when you’re finished, why not head over to their <strong><a href=\"https://grandpawasalion.bandcamp.com\">bandcamp</a></strong> to stream the other 5 tracks?</p>\n<p><iframe style=\"position: relative; display: block; width: 400px; height: 100px;\" src=\"https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/v=2/track=5636111/size=venti/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"400\" height=\"100\"></iframe></p>\n<p><iframe style=\"position: relative; display: block; width: 400px; height: 100px;\" src=\"https://bandcamp.com/EmbeddedPlayer/v=2/track=3940798651/size=venti/bgcol=FFFFFF/linkcol=4285BB/\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"400\" height=\"100\"></iframe></p>\n","slug":"11459-new-grandpa-was-a-lion-parispost-acid","category":"music","date":1316714327000,"wpid":11459,"isSticky":false,"featured_image":{"width":530,"height":360,"src":"2011/09/grandpa-was-a-lion.jpg","placeholder":"data:image/jpeg;base64, "},"createdAt":1587293790033,"updatedAt":1588403547207,"author":"5e9b68b27a1236eccfeb1d24","old_image":"2011/09/grand